      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KING BREW (2) led and was much too good for a maiden field over 1300m at this track, scoring by 3.5 lengths. Sparingly raced, and he has more to offer. Will skip over to the speed again and can take the next step. TORONADO ROCKET (3) resumed here in stronger and, as the betting suggested, he needed the run. He flies second-up and is right up to this at best. Will go close with average luck in the run. SETAGAYA (7) wound up strongly to finish 1.1 lengths adrift over 1200m this track/grade. Gives away starts, but she will hit the line hard and can't be ruled out. NEXT DESTINATION (5) found more like her best beaten 1L at Albany. Did well after a slow start, and she will be around the mark.",
